## 6. Base Styles

```css
html, body { width: 100%; min-height: 100%; background: #f9fafb; font-family: Inter, sans-serif; }
.dark html, .dark body { background: #101010; color: #a3a3a3; }
body { min-height: 100vh; font-size: 0.875rem; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; overflow-x: hidden; }
a:hover { color: #000; } .dark a:hover { color: #fff; }
.dark label { color: #a3a3a3; }
section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
*, ::after, ::before { border-color: #202020; }
.dark option { color: #fff; background: #181818; }
```

---

## 7. Interactive States Summary

| Element | Hover light | Hover dark |
|---|---|---|
| Button default | `bg-neutral-100` | `bg-monitor-gray-200` |
| Button highlighted | `bg-monitor` | `bg-monitor-100` |
| Button error | `bg-red-300` | `bg-red-800` |
| Box card | `bg-neutral-100` + child text black | `bg-monitor-100` + child text white |
| Monitor-box | `ring-monitor` | `ring-warning` |
| Menu item | `bg-neutral-300` | `bg-monitor-gray-100` |
| Dropdown item | `bg-neutral-100` | `bg-monitor` |
| Table row | `bg-neutral-200` | `bg-black` |

**Disabled universal**: `cursor-not-allowed`, transparent bg/border, `text-neutral-300` / dark `text-neutral-600`. Inputs keep filled disabled bg per input rules above.

---

## 8. Implementation Notes

- Extend `src/styles.css` `@theme` with `monitor`, `monitor-*`, `monitor-gray-*`, `warning-*`, `success`, `error`, `base` — map shadcn semantic tokens (`primary`, `background`, etc.) to Monitor values when adopting the system.
- Prefer Tailwind token classes (`bg-monitor-gray-100`) over raw hex in JSX.
- shadcn components: override variants via CVA to match Monitor patterns; keep Radix behaviour, swap visual classes.
- Composition over one-off markup — extract reusable `StatusIndicator`, `MonitorBox`, `Callout` when used more than once.
